  "text": "One study, which looked at the clinical features and treatment required in feet diagnosed antenatally, found that the degree of deformity was difficult to assess before birth. [CITATION_1] At birth, 26% were found to require no treatment, while 61% needed surgery. This has important implications for prenatal counselling. Antenatal diagnosis of any abnormality raises the issue of termination of the pregnancy. Given the results of the contemporary treatment of CTEV it is essential that families are adequately counselled before such a decision is made.",
